Neural Networks, Rule Learning, Theory. 

Neural Networks: The paper discusses the use of neural networks in the experiments to evaluate the effect of input representation on generalization performance.

Rule Learning: The paper also discusses the use of decision trees, which are a type of rule learning algorithm, in the experiments.

Theory: The paper discusses the theoretical concept of the importance of input representation in the accuracy of a learned concept description, and presents experiments to test this theory.
